Bruce Martin
1 September 2020

Today's reading covers computer networks. A very thorough read that covers the gamut of computer networking.

Types of computer networks:  LAN, WLAN, MAN, PAN, SAN, CAN, VPN

Terms and concepts:  IP address, Nodes, Routers, Switches, Ports, Network cable types.

Discussed the main types of network architecture: Peer to peer (P2P) and Client/Server.

Network topology:  Bus, Ring, Star Network and Mesh.

Also discussed security and mesh networks, load balance networks, and content delivery networks.
